==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[βαναυσικός]]''' (''banausikos'') "of or for mechanics", < '''[[βάναυσος]]''' (''banausos'') "mechanical, ironsmith", < '''[[βαύνος]]''' (''baunos'') "furnace, forge".

===Adjective===
# mechanical
# Ordinary, un-cultured.
===Quotations===
'''1957''': who almost by mistake pierced the hard '''banausic''' shell of Alexandria &mdash; Lawrence Durrell, ''Justine'', p.67 (Faber)

